.TH WM 1 "2026" "The-JLC-Project" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
wm \- display the current user's login name
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B wm
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B wm
retrieves and prints the login name of the user running the command.
This is a minimal JLC equivalent of
.BR whoami (1).
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success.
.TP
.B 1
Cannot retrieve user information.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Display current user:
.EX
wm
.EE
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR whoami (1),
.BR id (1)
.SH AUTHORS
The-JLC-Project contributors.

